
  <sn><md>### Space and Universe

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
**Space:** The limitless sky where our Earth, Sun, Moon, and innumerable stars, planets, and satellites exist. These ++celestial entities++ `move around space on their own axes at certain motions`.

**Extra-Terrestrial Bodies:** `Any celestial body found in the universe`. Examples include the ++Sun, Moon, planets, stars, comets, meteors, nebulae, pulsars, black dwarfs, and black holes++.

**Nature of the Universe:** Some celestial bodies have their own light, while others do not. The ++true size, nature, and form++ of the universe `remain largely unknown`. Some scientists ++believe++ it `has no beginning or ending`, while others believe it `has a definite form and diameter`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
